Description: Provides a flexible framework for fitting finite mixtures of 
    parametric frailty models with random covariates. Supports multiple baseline 
    hazards (exponential, Weibull, inverse Weibull, Gompertz, lognormal, 
    log-skew-normal, and loglogistic) and frailty distributions (gamma, positive 
    stable, inverse Gaussian, and lognormal). Implements cluster-weighted modeling 
    for profiling heterogeneous survival data with hierarchical structure.
